<rss xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" version="2.0"><channel><title>NBC News Top Stories</title><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/</link><description>NBC News Top Stories</description><language>en-US</language><copyright>© 2026 NBCNews.com</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 16:30:16 GMT</lastBuildDate><image><url>https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/MSNBC/Components/Media/NBC-promo-graphics/nbc-news.png</url><title>NBC News Top Stories</title><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/</link></image><item><dc:creator>Scott Wong</dc:creator><dc:creator>Melanie Zanona</dc:creator><dc:creator>Kyle Stewart</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Brennan Leach</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Lizzie Jensen</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 16:30:16 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Congress voted to fund most of the Department of Homeland Security, ending a 75-day shutdown. ICE and the Border Patrol will be funded separately because of Democratic opposition.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/congress-expected-end-record-75-day-partial-government-shutdown-rcna342903</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/congress-expected-end-record-75-day-partial-government-shutdown-rcna342903</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260417-capitol-hill-ch-1528-1fd938.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Alex Wroblewski</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Capitol exterior.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Homeland Security Secretary Markwayne Mullin had warned lawmakers that if they didn&#39;t pass funding by Thursday, emergency funding would run out and thousands of workers wouldn&#39;t be paid.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260417-capitol-hill-ch-1528-1fd938.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 16:30:16 GMT</pubDate><title>Record-long Department of Homeland Security shutdown ends</title><updateDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 20:58:24 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Aria Bendix </dc:creator><dc:creator>Brennan Leach</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 17:03:28 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>President Trump on Thursday announced a new nominee for surgeon general, Dr. Nicole Saphier. She replaces Trump&#39;s prior pick, Dr. Casey Means.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/trump-pulls-casey-means-nomination-general-replacement-nicole-saphier-rcna261423</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/trump-pulls-casey-means-nomination-general-replacement-nicole-saphier-rcna261423</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-casey-means-nicole-saphier-mn-1415-0c425d.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="800" width="1200"><media:credit>Getty Images</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Dr. Casey Means; Dr. Nicole Saphier.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Dr. Casey Means testifies at her Senate confirmation hearing on Feb. 25.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-nicole-saphier-mn-1400-9e8ae8.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>John Lamparski</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Dr. Nicole Saphier at Fox News Channel Studios in 2024. </media:text><media:description type="plain">Dr. Casey Means testifies at her Senate confirmation hearing on Feb. 25.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-casey-means-nicole-saphier-mn-1415-0c425d.jpg" height="800" width="1200"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 17:03:28 GMT</pubDate><title>Trump pulls Dr. Casey Means&#39; nomination for surgeon general, announces replacement</title><updateDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 20:01:39 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Ben Kamisar</dc:creator><dc:creator>Melanie Zanona</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Brennan Leach</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Bridget Bowman</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 13:37:14 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Louisiana is delaying its House primaries that were scheduled for May 16 to give state lawmakers time to redraw congressional maps there, after the Supreme Court struck down the current district lines in a decision with far-reaching consequences for control of Congress in 2026 and beyond</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/louisiana-delay-house-primaries-supreme-court-redistricting-ruling-rcna342858</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/louisiana-delay-house-primaries-supreme-court-redistricting-ruling-rcna342858</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-12/251221-jeff-landry-cc-1031p-57fb05.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1785" width="2500"><media:credit>Win McNamee</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Image: Lousiana Gov. Jeff Landry</media:text><media:description type="plain">Louisiana Gov. Jeff Landry is calling congressional Republicans to tell them about the plan to move back their primaries.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-12/251221-jeff-landry-cc-1031p-57fb05.jpg" height="1785" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 13:37:14 GMT</pubDate><title>Louisiana will delay House primaries after Supreme Court redistricting ruling</title><updateDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 19:02:50 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 17:11:38 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Sen. Elizabeth Warren, D-Mass., questioned Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth about traders appearing to benefit from &#34;inside information&#34; about developments in the Iran war.</description><expires>2056-04-30T17:10:43.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">f_mo_dc_warren_hegseth_trading_260430</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/video/warren-questions-hegseth-about-insider-trading-around-iran-war-developments-262470213623</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/f_mo_dc_warren_hegseth_trading_260430/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>Warren questions Hegseth about insider trading around Iran war developments</media:title><media:player url="https://www.nbcnews.com/video/warren-questions-hegseth-about-insider-trading-around-iran-war-developments-262470213623"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_04/1777569030702_f_mo_dc_warren_hegseth_trading_260430_S3_1920x1080-sv506w.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">Sen. Elizabeth Warren, D-Mass., questioned Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth about traders appearing to benefit from &#34;inside information&#34; about developments in the Iran war.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_04/1777569030702_f_mo_dc_warren_hegseth_trading_260430_S3_1920x1080-sv506w.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 17:10:38 GMT</pubDate><title>Warren questions Hegseth about insider trading around Iran war developments</title><updateDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 17:11:38 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Freddie Clayton</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 18:07:17 GMT</da